Inrush Current Limiting

USB specifies max 44 Ω || 10 µF VBUS load for 5 V.
We exceed that, so we must use an active circuit.
Both C109 and R117 define input current curve.
Values chosen by experimentation.

When using PD to negotiate 20 V, source is slew rate
limited by spec to handle 100 µF.
